@NODE DataFileFormat "Data file format..."

	Headlines/DataFileFormat
	========================

	The data file for quotes is a text file of the following format:

		---- start of file ----
		\\* PHRASE FILE
		\\* Breif description
		\\*

		%<CLASS 1>
		Class1 String 1
		Class1 String 2
		Class1 String 3

		%<CLASS 2>
		Class2 String 1
		Class2 String 2
		Class2 String 3

		%<CLASS 3>

		%MAIN
		Main String 1
		Main String 2

		%%
		---- end of file ----

	"%%"      - file terminator
	"%<CLASS> - defines a new class, this is followed by a series of
	            strings that make up that class, they may reference
	            other classes by using \CLASS. When \CLASS is found
	            a random string from that class is chosen and will
	            evaluated.
	"%MAIN"   - defines the main class strings. These are used as the
	            base to generate the phrases. See %<CLASS> for further
	            details.

@ENDNODE

